result.title: 1987 - 1987 Centre for Environment, Fisheries & Aquaculture Science (Cefas) North Sea Plankton Survey - RV Clione 06/87
result.name: 1987-1987-centre-for-environment-fisheries-aquaculture-science-cefas-north-sea-plankton-s-06-87
result.notes:
A series of five surveys were carried out between May and September of 1987 in 
the North Sea off the north-east coast of England to undertake stock 
assessment by the egg production method. The species targeted were *Nephrops 
norvegicus* (Norway lobster) and *Homarus gammarus * (European lobster) 
with plankton samples being collected at each site on a planned survey grid. 
The data described here consists of the numbers of eggs and larvae, along with 
associated positional and ancillary data and volumes filtered.
